            <div type="transcript" id="F578A">
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>The Angle of a Landscape -</l>
                    <l>That every time I wake - </l>
                    <l>Between my Curtain and<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 the Wall </l>
                    <l>Opon an ample Crack - </l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>Like a Venetian - waiting -</l>
                    <l>Accosts my open eye - </l>
                    <l>Is just a Bough of Apples - </l>
                    <l>Held slanting, in the Sky - </l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>The Pattern of a Chimney - </l>
                    <l>The Forehead of a Hill -</l>
                    <l>Sometimes - a Vane's<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 Forefinger - </l>
                    <l>But that's - Occasional - </l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>The Seasons - shift - my Picture - </l>
                    <l>Opon my Emerald Bough, </l>
                    <l>I wake - to find no - Emeralds -</l>
                    <l>Then - Diamonds - which the Snow<app type="division"><lem><pb/></lem></app>
 </l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>From Polar Caskets - fetched<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 me - </l>
                    <l>The Chimney - and the Hill - </l>
                    <l>And just the Steeple's finger - </l>
                    <l>These - never stir at all -</l>
                </lg>

            </div>     
